### Test protected endpoints (requires valid token)
### First login and copy the access_token from response

@token = your-jwt-token-here

### Get all users (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get user by ID (Logged in users only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{user_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update user (Logged in users only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/{user_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name"
}

###

### Delete user (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{user_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Test unauthorized access (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

